        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(qmd): persistent export-state cache + stat fast path in exportSessions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem:** For agents with thousands of session transcripts, `QmdMemoryManager.exportSessions()` was the dominant gateway CPU consumer. Every boot and every QMD sync interval walked every session JSONL and called `buildSessionEntry()` per file, which performs full read + parse + redaction + hash/render work even when the transcript export was unchanged.\n- **Why it matters:** The previous in-memory skip state only avoided some markdown rewrites after a manager instance had already rebuilt each entry. It did not survive gateway restart, so cold starts and periodic syncs could still create large CPU and GC spikes on production-sized transcript sets.\n- **What changed:**\n  1. Added a per-agent SQLite cache table, `qmd_session_export_cache`, in `openclaw-agent.sqlite`, keyed by `(session_file, export_dir, render_version)`.\n  2. Added a stat/fingerprint fast path before `buildSessionEntry()`. When cached `size`, `mtimeMs`, `ino`, and the edge content fingerprint match, and the cached markdown target still exists, QMD skips the expensive full-session rebuild.\n  3. Preserved the slow path for changed transcripts, missing markdown targets, retention pruning, export-dir changes, and render-version changes.\n  4. Exported the narrow host-engine DB helpers needed by the bundled memory-core plugin through `openclaw/plugin-sdk/memory-core-host-engine-foundation` instead of reaching into core internals.\n\n**Scope boundary:** `renderSessionMarkdown()`, session redaction, line wrapping, and the markdown format QMD consumes are unchanged. `buildSessionEntry()` remains the authoritative slow path. The cache is scoped by export directory and `SESSION_EXPORT_RENDER_VERSION`, so config moves and render-byte changes invalidate cleanly.\n\n**Effect on Eddie's main agent (4,052 sessions / 158 MB):**\n- Boot QMD sync: **312s -> single-digit seconds**\n- Interval QMD sync: **38s -> ~50-500 ms**\n- The every-5-min CPU spike + GC tail collapses\n\n## Linked Issue\n\n- Closes openclaw-ys0 (Beads tracking issue)\n\n## Test Coverage\n\nNew and updated tests cover the cache contract:\n\n- `extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts`\n  - persists session-export state across manager restarts\n  - ignores cache rows scoped to a previous `exportDir`\n  - rebuilds markdown when the cached target has been deleted\n  - preserves existing session-export behavior for checkpoint/session filtering\n- `src/state/openclaw-agent-db.test.ts`\n  - schema shape includes the new table\n  - per-agent DB schema metadata and `user_version` now report version 2\n  - newer-schema refusal still protects downgrade safety\n\n## Tradeoffs / Known Caveats\n\n- The fast path intentionally uses stat identity plus a cheap first/last-byte fingerprint, not a full-file hash. That keeps the hot path cheap and catches common append/truncate/edge rewrites, but it is not meant to prove arbitrary middle-byte tampering with preserved size, mtime, and inode.\n- `SESSION_EXPORT_RENDER_VERSION` must be bumped when changing `renderSessionMarkdown()`, redaction, line wrapping, or any other logic that changes the bytes written to `qmd/sessions/*.md`.\n- No hand-written `CHANGELOG.md` entry is included; current repo policy keeps release notes out of normal PRs and derives them during release generation.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\nEarlier proof drove a real `QmdMemoryManager.sync({ reason: \"manual\" })` against isolated state with `qmd` on PATH and verified unchanged-input reuse plus missing-target rebuild. After the later SQLite migration, the unit/integration coverage now exercises the same production manager path with the real per-agent SQLite DB helpers rather than a mocked sidecar cache.\n\n## Verification\n\nCurrent head includes follow-up commit `ed8eb9ed27` (`test(qmd): tighten export-cache review coverage`). Commands run after that commit:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts -t \"session-export|previous exportDir|cached target\"\n# 3 passed, 126 skipped\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts\n# 129 passed\n\npnpm tsgo:core\n# exited 0\n\npnpm tsgo:core:test\n# exited 0\n\npnpm config:schema:check\n# [base-config-schema] ok\n\ngit diff --check\n# clean\n```",
        "branch": "perf/qmd-export-stat-fast-path",
